   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF JEREMIAH MESSAGE TWENTY-FOUR ISRAEL'S SIN AGAINST JEHOVAH</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>JEHOVAH'S PUNISHMENT UPON ISRAEL 15 JEHOVAH'S PROMISE</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>CONCERNING THE RESTORATION OF ISRAEL 1 Scripture Reading: Jer 30 31</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Jeremiah 30 33 is a portion concerned with Jehovah's promise concerning the restoration of Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In this message we will begin to consider the various aspects of this promised restoration revealed in chapters thirty and thirty-one.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>I. JEHOVAH APPEARING TO ISRAEL FROM AFAR</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Jehovah appeared to Israel from afar from the wilderness where they followed Him 2:2b .</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Jehovah said that He loved Israel with an eternal love the bridal love 2:2a ; therefore, He has drawn them with lovingkindness 31:3 .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Jehovah went on to say, "I will build you again, and you will be built, / O virgin of Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>/ Again you will adorn yourself with your tambourines / And will go forth in the dance of those who make merry.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>/ Again you will plant vineyards / On the mountains of Samaria; / The planters will plant / And will partake of the fruit" vv.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>4-5 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>II.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>JEHOVAH TURNING THE CAPTIVITY</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>OF ISRAEL AND JUDAH</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Jehovah will turn the captivity of Israel and Judah and will bring them back to the land which He gave to their fathers, and they will possess it 30:3 .</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>A. Jehovah Telling Jacob Not to Fear</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>and Israel Not to Be Dismayed</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In verse 10a Jehovah declared that Jacob, His servant, should not fear and that Israel should not be dismayed.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>He would save them from afar, and their seed from the land of their captivity.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Then He promised, "Jacob will return and will be quiet and at ease, / And none will frighten him.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>/ For I am with you, declares Jehovah, to save you; / For I will make a full end of all the nations to which I have scattered you; / But I will not make a full end of you" vv.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>10b-11a .</S>
